22 "§ 116-209.62. North Carolina Teaching Fellows Program established; administration.
23 (a) Program. – There is established the North Carolina Teaching Fellows Program to be
24 administered by the System Office of The University of North Carolina, in conjunction with the
25 Authority and the Commission. The purpose of the Program is to recruit, prepare, and support
26 students residing in or attending institutions of higher education located in North Carolina for
27 preparation as highly effective teachers in qualifying licensure areas in the State's public schools.
28 The Program shall be used to provide a forgivable loan to individuals interested in preparing to
29 teach in the public schools of the State in qualifying licensure areas.State.
