21 SECTION 3.3.(a) Subsections (d) and (e) of G.S. 115C-472.22 read as rewritten:
22 "(d) Allocation of Funds. – Except as provided in subsection (f) of this section, the amount
23 received per average daily membership for a county shall be the difference between one hundred
24 ten percent (110%) of the State average current expense appropriations per student and the
25 current expense appropriations per student that the county could provide given the county's
26 wealth and an average effort to fund public schools. To derive the current expense appropriations
27 per student that the county could be able to provide given the county's wealth and an average
28 effort to fund public schools, multiply the county's wealth as a percentage of State average wealth
29 by the State average current expense appropriations per student. The funds for the local school
30 administrative units located in whole or in part in the county shall be allocated to each local
31 school administrative unit located in whole or in part in the county based on the average daily
32 membership of the county's students in the school units. If the funds appropriated for
33 supplemental funding are not adequate to fund the formula fully, each local school administrative
34 unit shall receive a pro rata share of the funds appropriated for supplemental funding.
35 (e) Formula for Distribution of Supplemental Funding Pursuant to This Section Only. –
36 The formula in this section is solely a basis for distribution of supplemental funding for
37 low-wealth counties and is not intended to reflect any measure of the adequacy of the educational
38 program or funding for public schools. The formula is also not intended to reflect any
39 commitment by the General Assembly to appropriate any additional supplemental funds for low-
40 wealth counties.counties. It is the intent of the General Assembly to incrementally increase
41 appropriations for the low-wealth allotment to provide eligible counties supplemental funding
42 equal to one hundred ten percent (110%) of the statewide local revenue per student by fiscal year
43 2027-2028. The State Board of Education shall adjust the formula to ensure each local school
44 administrative unit receives a pro rata share of the additional funds appropriated for the
45 low-wealth allotment in this section for supplemental funding."
