24 SECTION 3.12.(c) G.S. 115C-423 reads as rewritten:
25 "§ 115C-423. Definitions.
26 The words and phrases defined in this section have the meanings indicated when used in this
27 Article, unless the context clearly requires another meaning:
28 (1) "Budget" is a Budget. – A plan proposed by a board of education for raising
29 and spending money for specified school programs, functions, activities, or
30 objectives during a fiscal year.
31 (2) "Budget resolution" is a Budget resolution. – A resolution adopted by a board
32 of education that appropriates revenues for specified school programs,
33 functions, activities, or objectives during a fiscal year.
34 (3) "Budget year" is the Budget year. – The fiscal year for which a budget is
35 proposed and a budget resolution is adopted.
36 (4) "Fiscal year" is the Fiscal year. – The annual period for the compilation of
37 fiscal operations. The fiscal year begins on July 1 and ends on June 30.
38 (5) "Fund" is an Fund. – An independent fiscal and accounting entity consisting
39 of cash and other resources together with all related liabilities, obligations,
40 reserves, and equities which are segregated by appropriate accounting
41 techniques for the purpose of carrying on specific activities or attaining certain
42 objectives in accordance with established legal regulations, restrictions or
43 limitations.
44 (6) "Vending facilities" has the same meaning as it does in Local schools. – All
45 local school administrative units located in a county, plus any charter schools
46 that are attended by children residing in the county.
47 (7) Vending facilities. – As defined in G.S. 111-42(d), but also means any
48 mechanical or electronic device dispensing items or something of value or
49 entertainment or services for a fee, regardless of the method of activation, and
50 regardless of the means of payment, whether by coin, currency, tokens, or
51 other means."
