18 ISSUE CAPITAL BONDS
19 SECTION 3.13.(a) Purpose. – It is the intent of the General Assembly by this section
20 to provide, subject to a vote of the qualified voters of the State, for the issuance of four billion
21 dollars ($4,000,000,000) general obligation bonds of the State for the purpose of providing funds,
22 with any other available funds, for public school facilities through grants to counties for public
23 school capital outlay projects, repairs, and renovations.
24 SECTION 3.13.(b) Definitions. – Unless the context otherwise requires, the
25 following definitions apply in this section:
26 (1) Bonds. – Bonds issued under this section.
