34 CEP MEAL PROGRAM INCENTIVE
35 SECTION 5.5.(a) Part 2 of Article 17 of Chapter 115C of the General Statutes is
36 amended by adding a new section to read:
37 "§ 115C-264.15. CEP meal program supplement.
38 (a) Any public school unit or school within a public school unit that is operating a school
39 nutrition program that is eligible for the federal Community Eligibility Provision (CEP) program
40 shall participate in the CEP program to increase the number of students with access to healthy,
41 cost-free school breakfast and lunch. Schools participating in the CEP program shall have an
42 innovative breakfast option available where students have access to breakfast and are allowed to
43 consume breakfast in the classroom.
44 (b) To the extent funds are made available for the purpose, the Department of Public
45 Instruction shall issue State reimbursements to participating public school units and schools to
46 supplement federal reimbursements of school meals. State reimbursement shall equal the
47 difference between the federal free rate and the federal paid rate for the number of meals served
48 at the participating schools equal to a 0.2 multiplier of the Identified School Percentage (ISP) for
49 the participating schools. State and federal reimbursements shall not exceed one hundred percent
50 (100%) of the federal free rate of meals served. If funds provided for the purpose are insufficient,
51 the Department shall distribute available funds pro rata on the basis of average daily membership.
